FT  22 JAN 92 / UK Company News: Trading rise helps CMA to Pounds 2.05m
CENTRAL MOTOR Auctions lifted pre-tax profit by 13 per cent, from Pounds
1.81m to Pounds 2.05m, in the year to October 31. There was an exceptional
credit of Pounds 174,000 against a debit of Pounds 79,000.
Auction proceeds rose nearly 15 per cent to Pounds 330.3m and operating
profit was ahead 24 per cent to Pounds 1.53m (Pounds 1.23m). Net interest
received, however, fell to Pounds 344,000 (Pounds 653,000).
There was an increase of 6 per cent in sales of cars and light vans, and a
rise in the volume of vehicles sold in the heavy commercial vehicles sector.
The redeveloped sites at Wimbledon and Glasgow had shown good increases in
throughput of vehicles, with Glasgow particularly buoyant. The new site made
its first sale at the end of September.
Earnings per share were 11.66p (10.29p) and a final dividend of 3p makes a
total of 4p (3.5p).
